extends shared/layout

block body
  section.container
    .section-heading
      h1 Images
    .section-intro
      p The images library of glisten contain some simple styling for thumbnails as well as larger images.

    h2.sub-heading Thumbnails
    p.text-and-code.t-center
      sapn Thumbnails come in three sizes:
      code 120x120
      code 180x180
      code 240x240
      span :
    .image-thumbnails-examples
      .img-thumb.is-s
        img(src="http://placehold.it/120x120/4F4A4F/F2915C")
      .img-thumb.is-m
        img(src="http://placehold.it/180x180/4F4A4F/F2915C")
      .img-thumb.is-l
        img(src="http://placehold.it/240x240/4F4A4F/F2915C")

    p.text-and-code.t-center
      span Thumbnails are used by wrapping an
      code img
      span in
      code .img-thumb
      span and one of these size classes:
      code .is-s
      code .is-m
      code .is-l
    p.text-and-code.t-center
      span Images are resized to fit within their container. Thumbnails require rectangular images to not distort the image ratio.
    .image-thumbnails-examples
      .img-thumb.is-m
        img(src="http://placehold.it/320x320/4F4A4F/F2915C")
      .img-thumb.is-m
        img(src="http://placehold.it/480x480/4F4A4F/F2915C")

    h2.sub-heading Image with caption
    p.text-and-code.t-center
      span To give an image a caption, wrap it in a
      code .img-captioned
      span and add an
      code img
      span and
      code .caption
      span inside. Choose a size by adding one of these classes:
      code .is-s (320px)
      code .is-m (480px)
      code .is-l (640px)

    .image-caption-examples
      .img-captioned.is-s
        img(src="http://placehold.it/640x320/4F4A4F/F2915C")
        .caption
          p This is a caption - a good place for some info about the image.

      .img-captioned.is-m
        img(src="http://placehold.it/960x200/4F4A4F/F2915C")
        .caption
          p This image and its caption is 480px wide

      .img-captioned.is-l
        img(src="http://placehold.it/1200x320/4F4A4F/F2915C")
        .caption
          p.t-muted Yet another example, with some muted text.

    .tooltip.is-warning
        span Heads up! Captioned images are not responsive and will not degrade gracefully. Make sure you pick a suitable size!


